BLIS Version 0.9 README
=========================

Welcome to BLIS. BLIS is distributed under the Common Public License
Version 1.0 and is freely redistributable. All source code and documentation
is Copyright 2001-2007 by Lehigh University, Yan Xu, and Ted Ralphs. This
README may be distributed freely.

WHAT IS BLIS?
=============

BLIS (BiCePS Linear Integer Solver) is an application developed on top of
BiCePS and is part of the COPS library hierarchy. BLIS is a branch and cut
solver for Mixed Integer Linear Programs.


DOCUMENTATION
=============

The html documentation of the classes in BLIS (See INSTALL of BLIS) can be 
created. A user's guide that is under preparation that can help users to 
develop an application.


INSTALLATION
============

Please see the INSTALL file for a guide to installation.


CURRENT TESTING STATUS
======================

1. Configurations
   - Serial: well tested
   - LAMMPI: well tested
   - MPICH: well tested


